6(vii) The services of the full time daily wage employees, who
 have completed 10 years of service, after 1.1.2006, shall not be
 regularised;

(ii) The casual labourers thus engaged for a particular work
 cannot be regularised how so ever in any manner, without sanction
 of the post, scale of pay etc., by the Government;

terminus with the purposeful completion of the works concerned as
 per the Acts and the Rules in which such provisions for the
 deployment of casual labour is made;
